$string['choosereadme'] = '<div class="clearfix"><div class="theme_screenshot"><h2>Themes MB Lite</h2><img src="themesmb_lite/pix/screenshot.png" /><h3>Theme Discussion Forum:</h3><p><a href="http://moodle.org/mod/forum/view.php?id=46" target="_blank">http://moodle.org/mod/forum/view.php?id=46</a></p><h3>Theme Documentation:</h3><p><a href="http://docs.moodle.org/en/Themes" target="_blank">http://docs.moodle.org/en/Themes</a></p><h3>Report a bug:</h3><p><a href="http://tracker.moodle.org" target="_blank">http://tracker.moodle.org</a></p></div><div class="theme_description"><h2>About</h2><p>Themes MB Lite is a fixed-width, two-column theme for Moodle 2.2 or higher. The custom menu contains a Home link which always appears to the very left, and Login/Logout link, which appears after any administrator-added items.</p><p>Themes MB Lite has a settings page that lets you modify a custom footer and add custom css.</p><h2>Tweaks</h2><p>This theme is built upon Base, a parent theme included in the Moodle core. If you want to modify Themes MB Lite, we recommend that you first duplicate it then rename it before making your changes. This means you\'ll still have the original files if you make a mistake. More information on modifying themes can be found in the <a href="http://docs.moodle.org/en/Theme">MoodleDocs</a>.</p><h2>Credits</h2><p>This theme was coded and is maintained by Miriam Laidlaw of HRDNZ. She can be contacted by email at miriam@hrdnz.com.</p></div></div>';

